* What's this?
This is a Twitter client mainly using User Streams not API.

As chirp-client is using User Streams, favorites, retweets, replies, direct
messages, following activities, list activities as well as friend timeline are
shown almost in real-time. It is realized by continous HTTP connection (a
stream), not polling for Twitter server.

* Screenshots
See wiki. http://wiki.github.com/yanbe/chirp-client/ 

* Target platform
Linux desktop (especially GNOME on Ubuntu 10.4).

* Prerequiestics
If you are using Ubuntu 10.4, chirp-client  should run without prerequistics.

If you want to run this program on other platforms, please see head of
chirp-client.py and install non-standard Python modules you don't have.

* How to run
$ python chirp-client.py

